@node IMAGEFX "How to use this palette with ImageFX"

@{fg shine}    Netscape Palette V1.0@{fg shadow}

    8 January 1997

    @{b}ImageFX usage@{ub}

    Start ImageFX.

    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}L@{uu}oad@{fg shadow}@{ub}' to load the picture that you want to optimize.
    Select the filename of the picture that your want to optimise.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}O@{uu}k@{fg shadow}@{ub}'

    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}Palette@{fg shadow}@{ub}' to access the palette section.
    Click on the @{b}@{fg fill}cycle gadget@{fg shadow}@{ub} above the render button until it displays '@{b}@{fg fill}Render@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    This makes you work with the palette that's used for rendering.
    Click on @{b}@{fg fill}L@{u}o@{uu}ad@{fg shadow}@{ub} in the palette section to load a new palette.
    Select '@{b}@{fg fill}Netscape.col@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}O@{uu}k@{fg shadow}@{ub}'

    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}Render@{fg shadow}@{ub}' to access the rendering section.
    Click on the @{b}@{fg fill}cycle gadget@{fg shadow}@{ub} in the display options until it displays '@{b}@{fg fill}256@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    This makes ImageFX use 256 colours for rendering.
    Click on the left @{b}@{fg fill}cycle gadget@{fg shadow}@{ub} in the dither options.
    *   If it displays '@{b}@{fg fill}Float@{fg shadow}@{ub}', '@{b}@{fg fill}FloatR@{fg shadow}@{ub}', '@{b}@{fg fill}EDD@{fg shadow}@{ub}' or '@{b}@{fg fill}Order@{fg shadow}@{ub}' you will @{b}dither@{ub}.
    *   If it displays '@{b}@{fg fill}None@{fg shadow}@{ub}' you will @{b}remap@{ub}.
    Click on the right @{b}@{fg fill}cycle gadget@{fg shadow}@{ub} in the dither options until it displays '@{b}@{fg fill}High@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    This makes ImageFX use the best possible dithering/remapping algorythm.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}R@{uu}ender@{fg shadow}@{ub}' to optimize the picture.

    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}S@{uu}ave@{fg shadow}@{ub}' to save your picture.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}Rendered Image@{fg shadow}@{ub}' to save the optimized picture.
    Select the @{b}@{fg fill}fileformat@{fg shadow}@{ub} (preferably GIF or PNG).
    *   Select '@{b}@{fg fill}Save@{fg shadow}@{ub}' if you want to overwrite the original picture.
    *   Select '@{b}@{fg fill}Save as@{fg shadow}@{ub}' if you want to overwrite the original picture.

    @{b}Note@{ub}

    Experiment with the @{b}@{fg fill}dithering options@{fg shadow}@{ub} and rerender until the rendered picture looks right.

@endnode

@node PERSONALPAINT "How to use this palette with PersonalPaint"

@{fg shine}    Netscape Palette V1.0@{fg shadow}

    8 January 1997

    @{b}Personal Paint usage@{ub}

    Start PersonalPaint.

    Go to the '@{b}@{fg fill}Project@{fg shadow}@{ub}' menu and select '@{b}@{fg fill}Image format...@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    Use the slider next to '@{b}@{fg fill}Co@{u}l@{uu}ors@{fg shadow}@{ub}' until it displays the number '@{b}@{fg fill}256@{fg shadow}@{ub}' appears left of it.
    *   If you can't make it display 256, select another display mode.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}P@{uu}roceed@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.

    Go to the '@{b}@{fg fill}Color@{fg shadow}@{ub}' menu and select '@{b}@{fg fill}Palette -> Load...@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    Select '@{b}@{fg fill}Netscape.col@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}P@{uu}roceed@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.

    Go to the '@{b}@{fg fill}Brush@{fg shadow}@{ub}' menu and select '@{b}@{fg fill}Load...@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    Select the filename of the picture that your want to optimise.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}P@{uu}roceed@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.

    Go to the '@{b}@{fg fill}Settings@{fg shadow}@{ub}' menu.
    *   Select '@{b}@{fg fill}Dithering -> Pattern@{fg shadow}@{ub}' or '@{b}@{fg fill}Dithering -> Floyd-Steinberg@{fg shadow}@{ub}' if you want to @{b}dither@{ub}.
    *   Select '@{b}@{fg fill}Dithering -> None@{fg shadow}@{ub}' if you want to @{b}remap@{ub}.
    *   Make sure that the '@{b}@{fg fill}Dithering -> Best-Quality@{fg shadow}@{ub}' menuitem is selected.

    Go to the '@{b}@{fg fill}Brush@{fg shadow}@{ub}' menu and select '@{b}@{fg fill}Color -> Remap@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.

    Go to the '@{b}@{fg fill}Brush@{fg shadow}@{ub}' menu and select '@{b}@{fg fill}Save...@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.
    Select the @{b}@{fg fill}fileformat@{fg shadow}@{ub} (preferably GIF or PNG).
    Enter a new filename if you don't want to overwrite your original picture.
    Click on '@{b}@{fg fill}@{u}P@{uu}roceed@{fg shadow}@{ub}'.

@endnode

